The paper discusses spectral topic modeling algorithms, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. The focus of the paper is on improving the inference of document-specific topic compositions, which is a common problem in these fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
